""Noah,
I made it to Mouret safely.
It feels strange to return—it's been so long since we left.
The Ganelon may lie to the north, but the summers here were always just as vivid in my memory. The meadows, the streams, the markets… everything felt so alive.
I thought I'd never see it like this again, not after everything that happened. But when I stepped onto this land, the flowers and grass beneath my feet reminded me that life can still flourish, even after ruin.
I visited Father. The Wolfsbane is blooming beautifully.
I've enclosed one for you—maybe you can compare it to the ones in the castle's sunroom.
Oh, and… it's my birthday today. I wish you were here to celebrate with me, but reviving the Ganelon is my duty, and I won't stop until it's done.
Still, let's make a promise.
Next year, on this day, we'll stand together in Mouret—restored, alive—and admire the summer we both remember so well.
Goodbye, for now.""

""To _$$the future_$$:

 The War between the houses of Ganelon and Bathory has yet to cease. In the face of this historical inertia, our efforts feel exeedingly insignificant.
 Yet this does not mean our sacrifices were in vain. I shall continue to travel the continent, seeking new paths for the Bloodborn. Human blood is not essential—the Pure Blood Essence that I entrusted Mr. Cain to brew makes a perfect substitute. The Bloodborn need not forever hide in darkness; one day, we will surely walk beneath the sunlight.
 I leave this letter somewhere in Bathory Castle, hoping that its reader might set aside hatred and prejudice, and join me in welcoming that beautiful future.
 Even if it is destined to be a long, hard road.""
